<HEADLINE>
FT  07 JUL 94 / Commodities and Agriculture: Base metals prices end lower
after see-sawing day - Market Report
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Base metal markets finished a day of see-saw movements largely lower at the
London Metal Exchange as prices responded to short-term speculative
influences.
But traders said markets such as COPPER and ALUMINIUM retained a sound
undertone and were ready to retest the upside resistance at which their
recent rallies had stalled.
London Commodity Exchange robusta COFFEE futures finished near the day's
highs on the back of renewed talk about possible frosts in Brazil this
weekend. But COCOA prices, which notched up good gains during the morning
session, succumbed later to technically-inspired selling. 'There are a few
bears out there,' said one trader. 'When cocoa was knocked by selling
pressure, the support turned out to be pretty weak.'
Compiled from Reuter
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
