FT  07 JUL 94 / International Capital Markets: Bank scraps Dutch unit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CONNER MIDDELMANN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CS First Boston, the merchant banking arm of CS Holdings, plans to scrap its
Dutch equity operations in Amsterdam and move them to London within the next
few months, writes Conner Middelmann.
Mr Xavier Rolet, managing director of European equities at CS First Boston
in London, said that by concentrating equity operations in London, 'we want
to regroup our strength, develop our pan-European business and increase our
placing power among institutional and corporate clients.' The cost of
running the operation was a factor, although it was not decisive, he said.
CS First Boston is holding talks with the Amsterdam stock exchange 'to see
under what conditions we can continue as foreign-based members or in some
form of association,' Mr Rolet said. 'They have been fairly receptive.'
