</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Thomson-CSF, the French defence-based electronics company, yesterday
announced two joint ventures with Deutsche Aerospace (Dasa) in an attempt to
show that it had not been pushed off its expansionary course by losses from
the Credit Lyonnais bank that put it FFr2.3bn (Dollars 410m) in the red last
year.
The Thomson-CSF and Dasa joint companies are involved in 'smart' munitions
and missile propulsion. They would have a combined turnover of FFr1.9bn.
