<HEADLINE>
FT  07 JUL 94 / UK Company News: Record Pounds 7bn raised by flotations in
first half
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID WIGHTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A record Pounds 7bn was raised by UK and Irish companies floating on the
London Stock Exchange in the first half of the year. The figure was three
times the amount raised during the same period last year and more than the
total of Pounds 5.9m for the whole of 1993.
The first half's 141 new entrants was only 39 short of 1993's record of 180.
Despite the turbulent market conditions, 25 companies joined the Official
List in June but there has been a slowdown of new issues in the pipeline.
Mr Nigel Atkinson, head of listing at the Stock Exchange, said: 'With new
issuers becoming more cautious in the light of the current market
uncertainties, we may have to wait until conditions have settled before
seeing a resurgence.'
The strongest share price performance was from Utility Cable, which more
than tripled in the three months following its listing. Mithras Investment
Trust shares have risen 75 per cent and Trafficmaster by 42 per cent.
Flotations on the continent raised a total of Pounds 12.3bn in the first
five months of the year which included several large privatisations. But
only 32 new companies joined the large European Union exchanges in the
period, compared with 90 in London, excluding investment trusts.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
<IN>P6231 Security and Commodity Exchanges.
</IN>
<XX>
Types:-
</XX>
<TP>FIN  Share issues.
    FIN  Interim results.
</TP>
