FT  07 JUL 94 / World Cup '94: Tournament marks high and low points
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
World Cup highlights after 44 games:
Most goals in one game by one player: Oleg Salenko, Russia, five goals
against Cameroon, June 28; Russia won 6-1.
Most cards in one game: 10 cards in Italy-Nigeria, July 5 (nine yellows, one
red), and 10 in Mexico-Bulgaria, July 5 (eight yellows, two reds).
Largest crowd: 93,869 at US-Romania, Pasadena, June 26. Some 2.9m spectators
watched the first 44 matches.
Smallest crowd: 44,132, Nigeria-Bulgaria, June 21.
Most-watched game in the US: America's 1-0 second-round loss to Brazil, July
4, was the highest-rated soccer telecast ever in the US, Nielsen Media
Research said. ABC Television estimated that 32m viewers tuned in.
Penalties: 13 have been awarded in regulation time, and all produced goals.
