FT  06 JUL 94 / International Company News: Barclays quits Virgin Islands
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BERNARD SIMON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Barclays Bank has withdrawn from the US Virgin Islands, selling the bulk of
its business to Bank of Nova Scotia, writes Bernard Simon.
Terms were not disclosed, but Scotiabank said yesterday the deposit
liabilities and loan portfolio it had bought each amounted to about
USDollars 100m. The deal also includes a Barclays branch in St Thomas.
Scotiabank now has four branches in St Thomas and four in St Croix, as part
of an extensive presence in the Caribbean.
