FT  06 JUL 94 / International Company News: Hoechst to set up drugs joint
venture in China
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   FRANKFURT
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Hoechst, the German chemicals group, is to set up a pharmaceuticals joint
venture with the North China Pharmaceuticals Corporation, Reuter reports
from Frankfurt.
Hoechst said it would own 50 per cent of the venture which would have total
capital of DM38m (Dollars 23.3m).
NCPC is one of China's largest pharmaceuticals producers. The venture will
involve distribution and sale of medicines.
Hoechst said NCPC would market selected Hoechst products until the joint
venture's projected drug production facilities come on line at the beginning
of 1996.
