<HEADLINE>
FT  06 JUL 94 / London Stock Exchange: Dixons uncertain
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER JOHN, JOEL KIBAZO and STEVE THOMPSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Uncertainty ahead of full year figures from Dixons, the high street retail
group, and speculation of an investigation into trading practices saw the
shares dip 5 to 170p.
Dixons is forecast to announce a profit of between Pounds 70m and Pounds
82m, up from Pounds 35m last time, but the provisions could be quite high,
especially in relation to the recent sale of 100 of its Curry's elect-rical
stores. The write-down for Curry's is forecast at around Pounds 20m but some
analysts feel it could be substantially higher.
Also, there was a rumour that the Office of Fair Trading was planning an
inquiry into the pricing of white goods such as fridges and washing
machines.
