<HEADLINE>
FT  06 JUL 94 / UK Company News: Thorn poised to offload defence side
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BERNARD GRAY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Thorn EMI, the music and electronics rental company, is discussing the sale
of its remaining defence businesses with potential buyers.
Racal Electronics is thought to be the most likely buyer, but GEC has also
recently re-entered discussions. GEC withdrew from talks last year after due
diligence enquires had been conducted because a mutually acceptable price
could not be negotiated.
The businesses primarily manufacture radar, electronic warfare and
electronic command systems. Turnover last year was about Pounds 115m. Most
of the operations are based at Crawley, West Sussex.
GEC is thought to be interested because there is a good fit between Thorn's
business and its own electronic warfare operations.
The Ministry of Defence may be concerned about the threat to national
security if the business were sold overseas, though Thorn said it had no
reason to believe that the MoD had placed unusual constraints on the sale.
The current talks follow Thorn's agreement in principle to sell its defence
electro-optical and missile-fusing interests to Thomson of France at the end
of last month. Those businesses have turnover of about Pounds 80m.
</TEXT>
