<HEADLINE>
FT  06 JUL 94 / UK Company News: Neepsend up to Pounds 761,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Neepsend, the light engineer, reported pre-tax profits for the year to March
31 of Pounds 761,000, against losses of Pounds 99,000. Turnover increased
from Pounds 16.7m to Pounds 18.6m.
The company said the improvement had continued into the present year. The
shares rose 3p to 41p.
The result was after lower interest charges of Pounds 283,000 (Pounds
411,000) and an exceptional cost of Pounds 253,000 (Pounds 275,000) relating
to the sale of land on which the company will be entitled to extra payment
of Pounds 1m or Pounds 2m depending on planning permission.
Neepsend is also in talks on the disposal of its Canadian subsidiary which
should result in proceeds of Pounds 375,000.
Earnings per share were 2.12p (0.32p losses) and a final dividend of 0.75p
is recommended for a total of 1.25p (0.75p).
</TEXT>
